The paper discusses natural language processing and understanding, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The goal of making computers understand human language and offer assistance is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of semantic link models and algorithms also suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the challenges of comprehension in scientific literature, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the mention of modeling and designing new machine models suggests a focus on neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE).
